We recommended that Management:

Direct the GFPS, with the help of Municipal Planning and Development Office, to fast track the establishment of LGU’s database containing the sex-disaggregated data;

Direct the GFPS to perform gender analysis in identifying and formulating GAD issue to be addressed for a more gender-responsive GAD planning and budgeting; and

Conduct a capacity development on gender mainstreaming, gender analysis and gender assessment to empower GFPS on what should be done during GAD Planning and Budgeting phase.

Direct the BAC to strengthen internal control in scrutinizing the documents submitted by the bidders in order to identify those that are qualified and illegible to bid;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to evaluate the pertinent documents during pre-audit phase to ensure that the supporting documents of the disbursements to be paid is complete, appropriate and valid;


Direct the BAC to ensure that the SLCC of the bidders must be at least 50% of the ABC of the contract to be bid;

Direct the BAC to complete the procurement process before receiving the goods to be procured and stop the practice of advance delivery; and

Direct the Inspection and Acceptance Committee to ensure that all delivery of the goods procured shall be inspected especially those that are to be delivered by batch or in different schedules.

We recommended that Management direct the Program-in-Charge of the Community Based Training to include the required Competency Assessment activity as part of the program so that beneficiaries will have the chance of securing National Certificate, and to make the training worthwhile by attaining the stated objective of the conducting the training which is to help the beneficiaries land a job.

Before implementing a program, projects and activities, explore for some alternatives and administer a cost-benefit analysis;

Exercise due diligence in evaluating the effectiveness, efficiency and economic viability of each of the alternative and in choosing the best alternative that will generate the best results or benefits to the government and to the public; and

For the conduct of Community-based Training, coordinate with the TESDA to take advantage of possible scholarship grants to minimize the costs of conducting this program.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Establish responsibility center for GFPS under the Office of the Mayor;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to provide RC code in the eNGAs;

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to provide RC code in the Budget.

We recommended that management immediately:

direct the Municipal Budget Office to account and prepare reports of the collected admission fees from the abovementioned activities and remit these collections to the Municipal Treasurer;
direct the Municipal Treasurer to deposit the remitted collection from the admission fees and prepare reports to be submitted to the Accounting Office;
direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare necessary journal entry to records such revenue and also submit to the Office of the Auditor the report and the copy of the journal entry voucher; and 
require the Municipal Budget Office to submit written justification for not remitting the collections to the Municipal Treasurer and using the collection without proper recording and beyond the allocated budget of the programs and activities.

We recommended that management

conduct more comprehensive trainings/seminars to enlighten personnel dealing with garbage and waste emphasizing the importance and the possible effects of not wearing of PPEs during collection and transport schedule;
strictly require these personnel to wear the minimum required PPEs including the gloves, boots, and masks;
observe separate schedule of collection of specific types of wastes; and
redesign the garbage trucks and provide separate compartments and cover, as well as implement the prescribed marking in the body of the vehicle for proper identification as required by Section 24 of the abovementioned Republic Act.

