We recommended that management:
direct the Municipal Accountant to enforce strictly the deadline of each type of cash advances granted to officers or employees, and strengthen the operation of preventive and monitoring controls to ensure timely submission of liquidation documents;
require the Municipal Accountant to issue final demand letters to the concerned officers and employees for those cash advances that remained unliquidated for more than 90 days;
send final demand letters to those persons who have retired or out of service who still have unliquidated cash advances even to those whose whereabouts are already unknown (in that case send the letter to the last known address of the person); and
immediately file request for write off for those dormant unliquidated CA, and those which claimants are dead or with unknown whereabouts, after gathering the required documents to support that the condition for write off is existing.

